40|$|Kidney {{transplantation}} is {{the preferred}} treatment for many end stage renal disease patients; however, {{the small number of}} organs for transplantation does not allow all patients to have access to this scarce resource. An allocation system for deceased donor kidneys should be anchored to <b>transparent</b> <b>policies</b> and rules. It should take into account the relationship between supply and demand, hence seeking a balance between the higher net benefit of survival that can be provided by a particular organ and the transplant candidates’ waiting time (as well as the probability of being transplanted) ...|$|E
